text: (upbeat music)
- My name is Jessica Yang.

I'm a Senior Product Manager
at AWS Managed Services.
Being the Managed Services,

you pretty much cover
all aspects of the Cloud.
You learn everything about the Cloud
and that's just been so amazing.

I always knew AWS is a
fairly fast paced places
but the amount of scope of work it covers

and the project we
have, it's just amazing.

And lots of, offers so much
learning opportunities as well.
(upbeat music)
I'm working with a great org of people

who are incredibly talented,
super willing to help.

And even the leadership team,
I can ping them at any time.
And there was response.

I'm surprised they took me
because I'm being very honest

and upfront into my interview
process of like, I don't
have any Cloud management experience

but I think the mindset
here in AWS is as long

as you have a curiosity
to learn you are in.

And when I join, I'm like there's
so many training programs.

AWS is not just a great
place to put on your resume

but it's a great place
to make lifelong friends.
And it's a great place to learn
and make big impact on the work you do.
(upbeat music)
